{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop income tax on hospitality employees tips/gratuities",
        "additional_details": "The hospitality industry work extremely hard under a lot of pressure. People reward us and then we lose a large amount of that reward. We think Gratuities/ tips shouldn\u2019t be subject to income tax, and that it\u2019s unfair and undeserving. The hospitality industry is already understaffed, we think it can make it a lot harder to keep people when they are taxed on tips. It\u2019s a small bonus that people give of their own free will.",
        "background": "I\u2019d like the government to stop taxing employees on tips or gratuities.",
